## Naming Conventions

### Files & Directories
| Type | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| <e.g., React components> | <e.g., PascalCase.tsx> | `UserProfile.tsx` |
| <e.g., Utility modules> | <e.g., camelCase.ts> | `dateUtils.ts` |
| <e.g., Test files> | <e.g., *.test.ts, co-located> | `UserProfile.test.ts` |
| <e.g., Python modules> | <e.g., snake_case.py> | `user_profile.py` |

### Variables & Functions
| Type | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| <e.g., Functions> | <e.g., camelCase> | `getUserById` |
| <e.g., Classes> | <e.g., PascalCase> | `UserService` |
| <e.g., Constants> | <e.g., SCREAMING_SNAKE> | `MAX_RETRY_COUNT` |
| <e.g., Private methods> | <e.g., prefix with _> | `_validateInput` |
| <e.g., Boolean vars> | <e.g., is/has/should prefix> | `isLoading`, `hasPermission` |

### Database / API
- Table names: <e.g., snake_case plural — `user_events`, not `UserEvent`>
- Column names: <e.g., snake_case — `created_at`, not `createdAt`>
- API endpoints: <e.g., kebab-case — `/user-events`, not `/userEvents`>
- API response keys: <e.g., camelCase in JSON>

