## Error Handling

```<language>
# Pattern: <describe your error handling strategy>
# Example of the right pattern:
<code example>

# Anti-pattern — never do this:
<bad code example>
```

- **Never** swallow errors silently (`catch (e) {}` is forbidden)
- **Always** include context in error messages: not `"Not found"` but `"User {id} not found in users table"`
- **Error types:** <e.g., use custom error classes / use Result type / use typed error unions>
- **External service failures:** <e.g., always wrap in try/catch and log before rethrowing>

