## <Language-Specific Section>
<!-- Add a section specific to your stack. Examples below: -->

### TypeScript
- `strict: true` is non-negotiable
- No `any` — use `unknown` and narrow it
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes that others will extend; `type` for unions/intersections

### Python
- Type hints required on all public functions
- Use `dataclass` or `pydantic.BaseModel` for structured data — not plain dicts
- f-strings preferred over `.format()` or `%`

### Go
- Errors returned, not panicked (except truly unrecoverable states)
- Context propagated through all functions that do I/O
- Table-driven tests preferred

